
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes
class Provider {
  - name: String
  - location: String
}

class Cruise {
  - cruiseNumber: Integer
  - cruiseName: String
  - startDate: Date
  - endDate: Date
}

class Employee {
  - name: String
  - socialSecurityNumber: String
}

class Guest {
  - name: String
  - isVIP: Boolean
}

class Ship {
  - shipName: String
  - numberOfDecks: Integer
  - length: Double
  - passengerCapacity: Integer
}

class Booking {
  - bookingNumber: Integer
  - bookingDate: Date
}

class TravelAgency {
  - name: String
  - address: String
}

class DestinationArea {
  - areaName: String
  - seaName: String
}

class Show {
  - title: String
  - duration: Integer
}

class Ticket {
  - ticketId: Integer
}

' Define relationships
Provider "1" -- "0..*" Cruise : organizes
Cruise "1" -- "0..*" Employee : requires
Cruise "1" -- "0..*" Guest : has
Cruise "1" -- "1" Ship : uses
Cruise "1" -- "0..*" Booking : booked through
Booking "1" -- "1" TravelAgency : made by
Cruise "1" -- "0..*" DestinationArea : heads for
Cruise "1" -- "0..*" Show : offers
Guest "1" -- "0..*" Ticket : has
Ticket "1" -- "1" Cruise : belongs to

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Relationships:
- **Provider** organizes many **Cruises**.
- Each **Cruise** is managed by one **Provider**.
- A **Cruise** requires many **Employees**.
- A **Cruise** has many **Guests**, and a **Guest** can participate in multiple **Cruises**.
- A **Cruise** is associated with exactly one **Ship**.
- A **Cruise** is booked via one **TravelAgency** (each **Booking** is linked to a **TravelAgency**).
- A **Cruise** has a specific **DestinationArea**.
- A **Cruise** offers multiple **Shows**.
- A **Guest** can have multiple **Tickets**, but only one per **Cruise**.
- A **Ticket** belongs to exactly one **Cruise**.

